The paper discusses a distributed algorithm for principal component analysis (PCA) applied to a real domain name system (DNS) query dataset from a large network. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. Additionally, the paper evaluates the tradeoff between communication cost and solution quality, which could also place it in the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. The use of PCA as a network anomaly detection technique could also suggest the Learning (cs.LG) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) categories. Finally, the paper applies the distributed PCA algorithm to a specific dataset, which could place it in the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) category.
